9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 491, L.D. 1202, “An Act to Establish the
10 African American Studies Advisory Council and Provide Funding to Support African
11 American Studies”
12 Amend the bill in section 2 in §14 in the first indented paragraph in the 2nd and 3rd
13 lines (page 1, lines 9 and 10 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "serve as a resource to
14 educators, schools and the department to ensure" and inserting the following: 'monitor and
15 measure'
16 Amend the bill in section 2 in §14 by striking out all of subsection 5 (page 2, lines 1 to
17 19 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
18 '5. Curricula implementation. The advisory council shall use data gathered pursuant
19 to the representative statewide sampling conducted by the department under subsection 7
20 of African American studies curricula in school administrative units to establish a baseline
21 measure of the implementation of African American studies in school administrative units.'
22 Amend the bill by striking out all of sections 5 and 6 and inserting the following:
23 'Sec. 5. Teacher certification. The State Board of Education shall, no later than
24 July 1, 2026, evaluate whether the adoption of rules to require the completion of an African
25 American studies component in the qualifications for certifying teachers in accordance with
26 the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 20-A, sections 13012-A and 13013 is necessary. The
27 State Board of Education may adopt rules if the State Board of Education determines it
28 necessary.
29 Sec. 6. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
30 allocations are made.
31 EDUCATION, DEPARTMENT OF
32 African American Studies Advisory Council N549
33 Initiative: Provides base allocations to the African American Studies Advisory Council to
34 authorize expenditures of funds received from public or private sources.
